===Etymology===
{{L.}} {{term|academia}}. See {{term|academy}}. ''Academe'' (frequently capitalized) is a poetic name for the garden or grove near ancient Athens where [[w:Plato|Plato]] taught, supposedly named for its former owner, the hero [[w:Akademos|Akademos]].  Poetic references are often to "the groves of Academe", a translation of [[w:Horace|Horace]]'s ''inter silvas Academi''. [http://books.google.com/books?id=NHYXAAAAIAAJ&pg=RA3-PA169&dq=%22silvas+Academi%22&lr=&as_brr=1#PRA3-PA169,M1] [http://books.google.com/books?id=nVE3QD1Y5RAC&pg=PA14&dq=%22silvas+Academi%22&lr=&sig=pymz2Xcnaldixpke_6QPFsNSGxk]

